  "body": "# Feature Issue\r\n\r\nAllow user to reply and decline an identity verification request.\r\n\r\n![Drawer](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/46027/196442658-aec59614-8bb5-4ed1-b94d-868bd1e5cab0.png)\r\n\r\n### Acceptance criteria\r\n\r\n>Given that Carol received an identity verification request\r\n>When Carol presses \"Accept\"\r\n>Then she can reply in a text field directly from the existing notification\r\n>And she can write at most 280 characters\r\n\r\n>Given that Carol received an identity verification request\r\n>When Carol presses \"Accept\"\r\n>Then she is still able to decline the challenge by pressing \"Decline\"\r\n\r\n>Given that Carol already filled a valid answer\r\n>When she presses \"Send reply\"\r\n>Then the same notification changes its status to \"Replied\"\r\n\r\n### Out of scope\r\n\r\n- There's no need to implement the actual acceptance flow, as this is more complex and can be done using a separate issue. A dummy event handler might suffice.\r\n\r\n### Notes\r\n\r\n- It's going to be necessary to change the `activity-log` component to support the inline input text.\r\n- At the moment (2022-10-18), it's necessary to use the unmerged status-go branch https://github.com/status-im/status-go/tree/feature/activity-center-read-unread.\r\n\r\n### Figma\r\n\r\nIdentity request flows are described in https://www.figma.com/file/eDfxTa9IoaCMUy5cLTp0ys/Shell-for-Mobile?node-id=639%3A21926.",
